OL,3,CCovid nurse shares her experience as
OL,4,Cnew phase of inquiry starts
OL,6,F"Literally hour to hour things
OL,7,Fchanged, and more information was
OL,8,Fcoming through. The first night shift
OL,9,Fwe worked, we weren't aware we had to
OL,10,Fwear full PPE if a patient had a
OL,11,Fcardiac arrest."
OL,13,FOn the 23rd March 2020, the Prime
OL,14,FMinister announced the UK would go
OL,15,Finto a nationwide lockdown.
OL,17,FAndrea described how her job as a
OL,18,Fnurse changed instantly, as she and
OL,19,Fher colleagues were faced with the
OL,20,Fnew, terrifying challenges of the
OL,21,Fpandemic.
