OL,3,CCovid nurse shares her experience as
OL,4,Cnew phase of inquiry starts
OL,6,F"I don't think as a nurse you would
OL,7,Fever be coming to work and risking
OL,8,Fyour life as well as your family's".
OL,10,F"To have to ring people and tell them
OL,11,Ftheir loved one has COVID-19 and they
OL,12,Fprobably weren't going to see them
OL,13,Fagain and have that conversation over
OL,14,Fthe phone was awful."
OL,16,FAndrea, who is also a union
OL,17,Frepresentative at the hospital said,
OL,18,F"I do think it changed the face of
OL,19,Fnursing - it was terrifying."
